obo:HP_0000081 obo:IAO_0000115 A duplication of the collecting system of the kidney, defined as a kidney with two instead of, normally, one pyelocaliceal systems. The pyelocaliceal system is comprised of the renal pelvis and calices. The duplicated renal collecting system can be associated with a single ureter or with double ureters. In the latter case, the two ureters empty separately into the bladder or fuse to form a single ureteral orifice.
